# Write docs

Before creating or editing markdown in this repo, read and follow:

- `.cursor/skills/write-docs/SKILL.md`
- `.cursor/skills/write-docs/voice.md`
- `.cursor/skills/write-docs/gitbook.md`

## Required habits

- Job-first page leads (no gateway appositive)
- Frontmatter `description` answer-first (~150–160 chars) on hubs/new pages
- Keep `SUMMARY.md` in sync; each markdown file once; spaces for indent
- Relative internal links only
- End with **Related** (3+ links when useful); glossary acronyms → `prestd/acronyms.md`
- Honest database support labels; no unshipped install claims

## Verify before done

- [ ] Lead answers the page question
- [ ] SUMMARY updated if URLs changed
- [ ] Relative links resolve
- [ ] GitBook blocks used only where they help
